data.description: Wow! 2.75% assumable VA loan for those who qualify--check with your loan officer. It's rare that a home of this size and quality comes on the market.... There are so many things to rave about here. Located on a forested lot on a very quiet street,  you'll have all the privacy you could hope for and there’s plenty of parking for whatever recreational toys you may have. It's a beautiful house, the curb appeal is stellar. Inside, huge rooms are the name of the game--the architect must've been from Texas! The main level features hardwood floors in most rooms and an updated kitchen with gorgeous granite tops and appliances. There's a great sunroom with cathedral ceiling merging indoor and outdoor worlds. The lot is quite level, given that the home is in the mountains. Upstairs you'll find two full baths and three massive (we talked about this) bedrooms with new LVP flooring. The home has a propane-fueled 11 kW generator. A great side-entry garage completes the exterior look. Come see this beauty quickly. A home like this doesn't come on the market often. This is your chance!
